## Definition

For $X$ a [[scheme]] or more generally an [[algebraic stack]], let $X_{et}$ be its [[small Ã©tale site]]: the full [[subcategory]] of the [[slice category]] $Aff/X$ on the [[Ã©tale morphism]]s equipped with the induced [[Ã©tale topology]].

Then the [[category of sheaves]] $Sh(X_{et})$ is called the **Ã©tale [[topos]]** of $X$. 

This is the [[little topos]]-incarnation of $X$.

